 Former President, Chief Olusegun Obasanjo is meeting with the 30 parents of the remaining missing Chibok girls at the Olusegun Obasanjo Presidential Library (OOPL), Abeokuta. The meeting which facilitated by the Murtala Muhammed Foundation (MMF) was part efforts to reassure and counsel Â the families on the development. The leader of delegation and Head of Operations of the Foundation, Funmi Adesanya told newsmen that invitation was at the instance of the former president, who is also the Chairman of the Board of Murtala Muhammed Foundation.